additional_info:
Yeah and I don't know how to change the color of the arrow sorry it didn't really bother me that much so

Edit line 18-29 into

div.nipple {
display:none !important;
}

to get rid of the arrow, if it bothers you or disrupts your theme

css:
@namespace url(http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml);

@-moz-document url-prefix("http://www.tumblr.com"), url-prefix('https://www.tumblr.com')   {

p.asker {
    position: absolute !important;
    left: 13.5% !important;
    top: 100% !important;
    display: block;
    font-weight: normal !important;
    font-size: 0px !important;
    margin: 26px 2px 0px !important;
}
span.name, a.name {
    font-weight: normal !important;
    font-size: 12px !important;
}
div.nipple {
    position: absolute !important;
    left: 6% !important;
    top: 100% !important;
    display: block;
    -webkit-transform: rotate(90deg);
    -moz-transform: rotate(90deg);
    border-top: 0px solid !important;
    border-bottom: 0px solid !important;
    border-left: 0px solid !important;
    margin: 9px 4px 0px !important;
}
div.avatar {
    float: left !important;
    padding: 0px 14px !important;
    margin: 0px 0px 10px !important;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(227, 227, 227) !important;
    width: 100% !important;
}
div.avatar.small_avatar {
    width: 0% !important;
    margin: 0px 0px 0px !important;
    padding: 0px 16px !important;
}
div.inner_frame {
    width: 0% !important;
    margin: 0px 0px 0px !important;
    padding: 0px 0px !important;
}
div.avatar:after {
    content:"there's nothing to see here";
    font-size:0px;
    position: relative !important;
}
div.note_item {
    background-color: rgb(230, 234, 237) !important;
    border: 0px solid rgb(217, 217, 217) !important;
    padding: 14px 14px !important;
    width: 500px !important;
    font-weight: bold !important;
    font-size: 18px !important;
    margin: 0px 0px 14px !important;
}
}
